:{{see|vela}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the French [[astronomer]] Nicolas Louis de Lacaille in 1763. From {{L.}} ''[[vela#Latin|vela]]'' (''pl.'' of ''[[velum#Latin|velum]]''), the "sails of a ship"
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Vela (constellation)}}
'''Vela'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[spring]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to resemble the [[sail]]s of a [[ship]]. Until 1763, it was part of a larger constellation, [[Argo Navis]].

